fullText:
Messiness is opportunity during platform shifts.

In the 90s DOS era, every word processor had to reinvent the wheel: writing its own print drivers and clipboard just to function.

@stevesi recalls how bundling those into the platform changed everything. Apps could finally talk https://t.co/reg3thTFeJ

"GPT wrapper" was meant as a derogatory term, but it completely misses the point.

Nobody called software on the cloud a "cloud wrapper."

@martin_casado: "These models are an evolution in infrastructure, and there's tremendous opportunity to add value above the stack." https://t.co/fzrucX0BPN
